Comedian AY Makun has lamented the state of affairs in the nation following Monday’s Kaduna-Abuja train terrorist attack and chaos at the Moshood Abiola Stadium, Abuja on Tuesday after the Super Eagles’ failure to qualify for the Qatar 2022 World Cup. The award-winning comic star argued the entire country was in dire need of complete overhauling. According to him, some important changes have to happen in some crucial areas of the country if it must function maximally.   Ex-BBN Tacha, Mercy Ike reconcile     Mayorkun blames FG for Kaduna train attack     Sharon Ooja, Kate Henshaw attend Netflix party in SA   “Nigeria as a country should be taken to the mechanic workshop for servicing. They are several fluids that should be kept at the appropriate levels to help keep the country running properly. Especially the engine oil, power steering, and transmission fluid,” he wrote. The funnyman added: “That na if mechanic no ask us to buy a new engine. Because (there) are some drivers that need to be paid a courtesy visit by Bianca and Will Smith.”